1.title: Episode #7.1
1.plot: Jay Sutay is a comedian at night but by day, a pediatrician. Laura Steele wants to share stories of her privates.

2.title: Episode #7.2
2.plot: Kandyce August lost a lot of weight to get back into the dating pool. Mike Kramer talks us where it went wrong for him.

3.title: Episode #7.3
3.plot: Purohit has a daughter that prevents him from getting sex from the wife and Sandy Bernstein discusses her weight loss.

4.title: Episode #7.4
4.plot: Glen Tickle (yes, that's his real name) talks about his life as a substitute teacher with his last name. Think Floyd shares his secret on keeping his house from getting robbed.

5.title: Episode #7.5
5.plot: Caitlin Arcand talks about a gig she did in Ohio. Tom Paciaffi shares his feelings on being recently married.

6.title: Episode #7.6
6.plot: Sal LoPizzo is a self-described, "Gay Goomba," who was disowned by his parents...when he moved to Jersey. Natasa Warasch regales us about her first time in NYC.

7.title: Episode #7.7
7.plot: Linette Paladino shares stories of being a female in the Army while stationed in Iraq. John Sweeny married into a Colombian family that won't let him say goodbye while kissing and hugging everyone in sight.

8.title: Episode #7.8
8.plot: Tim Warner thinks we live in the Matrix while Cliff Mula describes life in the hood of Hartford, Connecticut.

9.title: Episode #7.9
9.plot: Phillip Anthony talks about being recently getting married. And Ibrahim Khalif shares stories of being a high school janitor.

10.title: Episode #7.10
10.plot: Liz Russo shares stories about quitting drinking because of 2 DWIs. And Henry Epstein is a gay man living back home with his mom, grandmother, and cats.

11.title: Episode #7.11
11.plot: Eryca Nolan has a teenager she's not too fond of (at times) and Tony Brooklyn thinks we should end it all Thelma and Louise style.

12.title: Episode #7.12
12.plot: RA discusses how his autism affects others and Vinnie shares his life living with his single mom and several sisters.

13.title: Episode #7.13
13.plot: The panel votes on the winner for S7 as well as shouts out some of their favorite comedians.

1.title: Episode #1.1
1.plot: Chanel Ali, Lindsay Theisen, Gerald Delgado, Jason Scoop, Ralph Anthony, and Doug Max all perform in the inaugural episode of Comics Watching Comics. We also get to know panelists Leah Bonnema and John Moses to learn more about their careers in stand up comedy.

2.title: Episode #1.2
2.plot: Jeff Paul and Pudge Fernandez see if they have what it takes to get laughs from the panel.

3.title: Episode #1.3
3.plot: Ben Long and Joe Romby Jr. peddle their comedic wares for the panel. See if they get the thumbs up or thumbs down.

4.title: Episode #1.4
4.plot: Alexa and Matt think they're good enough to win it, does the panel agree?

5.title: Episode #1.5
5.plot: John Trumbull is discusses his time travel method while John Minus goes through life as a soft spoken black man.

6.title: Episode #1.6
6.plot: Shareef Reef talks about being confused as an Uber driver and Evan breaks down the logic of an alien invasion.

7.title: Episode #1.7
7.plot: Teresa talks about dating life in NYC while Jeremy discusses other guys hitting on his girlfriend. And Peter Pan closes out the season with some original crowd work. Lastly, the panel selects their winning comedian for season 1.

1.title: Episode #2.1
1.plot: New year, new panel. Joining Kevin Gootee on the couch are Mike Recine, Cyrus McQueen, and Brian Jian. And in our first episode we have Elsa Waithe telling us how much she hates the film, Frozen. And JC Knows Best has a certain "type" of lady.

2.title: Episode #2.2
2.plot: Tracie Jayne shares her adventures of being in the Navy as well as a bartender. And Jakub Haczkiewicz has some thoughts on his large forehead. Lastly, Cyrus McQueen tells his best heckler story in our "2 Drink Minimum."

3.title: Episode #2.3
3.plot: Michael Brooks is a teacher from Philadelphia who also has some remaining college debt and Joan Weisblatt has a special hiding place for her cell phone. In our "2 Drink Minimum," Mike Recine talks about his best heckler story and he also shares what he thinks makes a great comedian.

4.title: Episode #2.4
4.plot: Will Carey was in a punk rock band and Pamela Rae brings us into her dating life with Tourette's.

5.title: Episode #2.5
5.plot: Adam Foster had a teacher who got busted for having sex with a student. And Misha Han talks about going to college at 16 while dealing with bullies. Finally, Cyrus McQueen shares what annoys him about newer comics in our "2 Drink Minimum."

6.title: Episode #2.6
6.plot: Neko White gives his thoughts on Harriet Tubman going onto the 20 dollar bill. And Jeff Young talks about how the Spanish flu killed his ancestors.

7.title: Episode #2.7
7.plot: Matt Lajeskie despises long Facebook posts and Mike Kerrigan discusses his workout therapies. Lastly, Lawrence Deloach has a storied history of getting fired from jobs.

8.title: Episode #2.8
8.plot: Phil From Chico takes a call on stage from his brother...in prison. L Michelle is annoyed she's not getting stop and frisked enough.

9.title: Episode #2.9
9.plot: Jose Vegas has some good NYC stories and Anthony Crescenzo's mom is scared of him living in Harlem.

10.title: Episode #2.10
10.plot: Tony Brooklyn has some advice to meet women after the bars close and Ken Perlstein has a son who gives him fits.

11.title: Episode #2.11
11.plot: Mo Vida hates her friends' Facebook posts that share too much information about their kids. And Peter Keepnews tells youngins about something nostalgic, the radio.

12.title: Episode #2.12
12.plot: Anthony Ennis has a 5'10" daughter that has hopes to play in the WNBA. And a champion shall be crowned as the panel selects their winner for this group.

1.title: Episode #3.1
1.plot: Here we go. Chris Crespo comes out of the gate to share stories of being a substitute teacher. Michelle Conrad has a child who is an aspiring comedian and Ray Gootz shares how he passes time on the road in our "2 Drink Minimum."

2.plot: Ron Barba wants to you to know how he escaped corporate America's clutches and Natty Bumpercar has a couple of cats with quite curious names.

3.title: Episode #3.3
3.plot: Laura High shares here family ancestory report while Billy Procida gives a few nuggets about Craig's list encounters. And Richie Redding tells you just how hard it is to make it in comedy.

4.title: Episode #3.4
4.plot: Geoffrey K has a teenage son who got busted for weed while Dave Hoj shares his diet tips.

5.title: Episode #3.5
5.plot: Mindy Matijesevic talks about life after divorce while Fumi Abe talks about being Japanese and growing up in Ohio. Mike Gaffney talks about what annoys him most about comedians in our, "2 Drink Minimum" segment.

6.title: Episode #3.6
6.plot: Craig McLaughlin likes to scare people on elevators and Rishi Mathur has been mistaken for other cultures.

7.title: Episode #3.7
7.plot: Eli Lebowicz goes through how being Jewish can affect routine occurrences. And Big Kevin Mason guesses what a black guy would do if he were to star in a Al-Qaeda beheading video.

8.title: Episode #3.8
8.plot: We hear about Brian Rabadeau's encounter with a much older woman and Bob Kitson discusses how he and his ex-wife deal with their kid.

9.title: Episode #3.9
9.plot: Tara Cannistraci gives you insight on her dating life and Glenn Cohen tells us about a time on set he had with Holly Hunter. And in our "2 Drink Minimum," Richie Redding tells us how Katt Williams discovered him and put him on his national tour.

10.title: Episode #3.10
10.plot: Dan Howlett brings us into his world of an Englishman living in America. And Phillip O'Reilly enlisted into the Air Force at 19 and got a funny nickname.

11.title: Episode #3.11
11.plot: Rob Santos has been told he looks like the Statue of Liberty on crack and Kathy Arnold knows how to save a few bucks. Groupie stories with Mike Gaffney are the theme for this segment of "2 Drink Minimum."

12.title: Episode #3.12
12.plot: Ray Vazquez shares his experiences while being super high and the panel selects their winner for season 3.

1.title: Episode #4.1
1.plot: BOOM. We kick off a brand new season with Joe Eichler as he talks about his misfortunes his phone that loves to autocorrect. The new panel includes: Jim Mendrinos, Sean Lynch, Amy Shanker, and master panelist Jeffrey Gurian.

2.title: Episode #4.2
2.plot: Gerard Haran takes us into the world of a millennial that doesn't want to be a millennial. Molly Horan talks about slowly coming out as bisexual to her mother. And we end with Jim Mendrinos in our "2 Drink Minimum" discussing what he thinks makes a winning comedian.

3.title: Episode #4.3
3.plot: Comedian Clay Miles is an outlaw...in his own basement. And we learn what secret ingredients Amy Shanker is looking for in a winner.

4.title: Episode #4.4
4.plot: Thomas Liquori isn't a fan of social situations, especially BBQs. And Reid Clark does a parody of the Cha-Cha Slide, policeman remix. And in our, "2 Drink Minimum," we hear the best advice given to Sean Lynch.

5.title: Episode #4.5
5.plot: Rhonda Hansome shares her experiences of almost becoming a nun. And Jim Mendrinos tells us how he dealt this comedians who stole his material.

6.title: Episode #4.6
6.plot: Duanne Williams gives his take on Jamaican nannies taking care of white kids. And Ann Walker breaks down what Michael Jackson was saying in one of his songs.

7.title: Episode #4.7
7.plot: JJ Mattise goes through the horrors of buying a plan B pill.

8.plot: DJ Doke discusses his dating preferences and Kandace Saunders tells you why she hates social media.

9.title: Episode #4.9
9.plot: Michael Lancer shares his feelings on turning 40. And in our, "2 Drink Minimum," we learn how Amy Shanker passes time on the road.

10.title: Episode #4.10
10.plot: Jennifer Gable brings us to her world as an actress and Andrew Vu has a grandmother that may be a little bit racist. And Jeffrey Gurian gives you his keys to being a successful comedian.

11.title: Episode #4.11
11.plot: Sarah Garner claims she can cry at the drop of a dime while Sal Coladonato tells us about being a NYC construction worker. And Jeffrey Gurian tells us how hard it is to make it in comedy in our segment, "2 Drink Minimum."

12.title: Episode #4.12
12.plot: In the conclusion for season 4, the panel votes on the winning comic to perform at the live showcase. Congrats to the winner and great job by all those who performed.

1.title: Episode #5.1
1.plot: Season 5 kicks off with a new crop of comedians and of course, a brand new panel. This year's panel consists of Geno Bisconte, Mark Riccadonna, and Mark DeMayo. Master panelist Jeffrey Gurian is back to give his thumbs up or down on the panel's choice of the winning comic. Here, we see Oniyide Francis give his take on life in the Bronx. And Jonezy Karona discuss his neck tattoos as well as the perception of having said tattoos.

2.title: Episode #5.2
2.plot: Kevin Francois has a LOT of kids and shares his parenting techniques. Pauline Murphy is a "convenient" feminist and breaks down cat calling men.

3.title: Episode #5.3
3.plot: Derrick Cakley loves making people miss their exits on the highway. And Kathryn Gironimi lost her virginity at a later age. We also hear from Mark DeMayo and his thoughts on what's wrong with comedy today in our "2 Drink Minimum" segment.

4.title: Episode #5.4
4.plot: Ever wonder what goes on at a gay orgy? Jeffrey Marx has been there and adds a few things he'd like to see at the next one. Alex Simmons went to theater camp and shares his experiences.

5.title: Episode #5.5
5.plot: Cory Chappo starts us off with his interpretation of what hell will be. Vanetta Schoefield weighs the pros and cons of dating men and women. And Mark Riccadonna shares a story while on a USO tour in our "2 Drink Minimum."

6.title: Episode #5.6
6.plot: T Ray Sanders tells us how the journey of standup comedy is obviously a rough one. And Kaitlyn Murphy takes us for a ride with some good drunk stories. In our "2 Drink Minimum", Mark DeMayo gets into the transition of a cop into a comedian.

7.title: Episode #5.7
7.plot: Krystal Dyer is a recent divorcee and isn't thrilled with the dates she's been on. Tom Mongelli comes from a very Italian family in Jersey. Lastly, we hear Geno Bisconte ponder about what he might have done if it weren't for comedy in our "2 Drink Minimum."

8.title: Episode #5.8
8.plot: Sean Savoy had a date that went terribly wrong while Tim Ely goes over the checklist of things that suck.

9.title: Episode #5.9
9.plot: Evan Jones from Season 1 returns and this time, he talks about the show, "Scared Straight." And Faisal Alam isn't your typical Muslim. Lastly, Mark Riccadonna shares key points on what makes a winning comic.

10.title: Episode #5.10
10.plot: Onika McClean has a teenage daughter that's quite a handful. Marcus Madness wears a robe because he says he got thrown out of his house. And Geno Bisconte tells his best bombing story in our "2 Drink Minimum."

11.title: Episode #5.11
11.plot: Howard Lester has great stories as a gay comedian. And Chimmie Hernandez is a germaphobe from the wrong town to be a germaphobe...Las Vegas. In our "2 Drink Comedian" segment, Mark Riccadonna says what he hates about newer comics.

12.title: Episode #5.12
12.plot: John Kurschner tells us about a haircut that he's not too fond of. And Jepherson Guevara learned English like most foreigners have, American TV.

13.title: Episode #5.13
13.plot: Adam Podell has an interesting relationship with his dad. Also, Felix Gussone tells us his about migration from Germany to the United States.

14.title: Episode #5.14
14.plot: The finale is here. The boys vote for the winning comedian of this season. Does Master Panelist Jeffrey Gurian agree with the panel's choice?

1.title: Episode #6.1
1.plot: Leola Stafford kicks it off with tales from living in Detroit while Alex Barry breaks down the finer points of horror and porno films. Carole Montgomery gives great scoop about dating amongst comics.

2.title: Episode #6.2
2.plot: Courtney Reynolds tells us what it's like living a with girl's name from the Poconos and Steve Keirstead talks about his dating life. In our "2 Drink Minimum," the lovely Gina Brillon tells one of her bombing stories.

3.title: Episode #6.3
3.plot: Maurice Green is a self described ugly guy who is dating an ugly woman with ugly kids. Keenan Steiner shares his story of being half Italian, half Jewish, and gay. And Jason Scoop shares one hell of a groupie story in our "2 Drink Minimum."

4.title: Episode #6.4
4.plot: Alex Engelbert has some interesting stories about getting back at her cheating ex boyfriends. And Eric Tabach shares stories about growing up in Russia. Carole Montgomery tells us what grinds her gears regarding newer comics in our "2 Drink Minimum."

5.title: Episode #6.5
5.plot: John Fox shares a story about his younger sister whose dance studio has a curious name. Danny Klau works at SNL as a cue card guy and is worried about being replaced by machines. Lastly, Gina Brillon spills the beans about if she dated a fellow comic in "2 Drink Minimum."

6.title: Episode #6.6
6.plot: Nick Carra is a bad influence on his nephew and Joy Lane is a Muslim that served in the Navy. Finally, Jason Scoop talks about the comedians he thinks that have a leg up in the game.

7.title: Episode #6.7
7.plot: John Tansey is a showtime fan that loves to sing through his act and Anish Mitra talks about going to his college reunion. And Carole Montgomery shares her defining moment in comedy.

8.title: Episode #6.8
8.plot: Gab Austein brings us into her dating world and Mike Keegan shares stories about living at home with his mom. Finally, Gina Brillon shares stories of her debating about quitting comedy.

9.title: Episode #6.9
9.plot: A Marie Castillo is a tall lady and she's a big sports fan and Will Cheng was a former fitness model. In conclusion, Jason Scoop talks about being on Dana Carvey's show, "First Impression."

10.title: Episode #6.10
10.plot:
Know what this is about?

11.title: Episode #6.11
11.plot: Serge Santana's dad was a janitor in school and Kenan Floyd was knocking at your doors on a Saturday morning. You guessed it, a Jehovah's witness.

12.title: Episode #6.12
12.plot: We come to a close and vote on the winner. Who takes the prize and appears at the Live Showcase?

-1.title: Comics Watching Comics Live Show!
-1.plot: Reward time. This is the live showcase at Gotham Comedy Club for all of the season winners, panelists, as well as redemption seekers. The redemption seekers are comedians who had a rough set and get a chance to do one minute. The audience votes on their favorite comic and the winner gets to do a full set this same night. Who wins redemption?

locations: New York City, New York, USA
imdb.plot outline: Intermediate comics perform their sets which are viewed by a panel of more tenured comics. The panel selects a winner to perform at the live showcase. The home audience plays along by voting for their favorite panelist on Twitter (@Comicswatching) and Instagram (Comicswatchingcomics) that they want to join the All-Star Panel.
